tectionist stance, the desire to make property of knowledge, can black feminists reimagine intellectual production in ways that unleash black feminist theory's visionary world-making possibilities.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Sep 2020) 0aFeminismzUnited States. 0aFeminist theory. 0aIntersectionality (Sociology) 0aIntersectionality (Sociology). 0aUniversities and collegeszUnited StatesxSociological aspects. 0aWomanismzUnited States. 0aWomen's studieszUnited States. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Ethnic Studies / African American Studies.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDUK eBook-Package 2019z978311069632540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781478002253zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781478002253423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781478002253.jpg  a978-3-11-069632-5  DUK eBook-Package 2019b2019  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles